trans-unit.source: Defines the interface for an STL/CLR [priority_queue](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/4d0000d3-68ff-4c4b-8157-7060540136f5) object.
The type of an element in the controlled sequence.
The type of the underlying container.
Replaces all elements of the container.
For more information, see [priority_queue::assign (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/00cd3623-ecd0-4dde-ba5c-777c1c0bc0b5).
The container adapter to insert into the container.
Determines whether the container contains no elements.
For more information, see [priority_queue::empty (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/bb2bc4cf-395f-4c4f-b432-550b85e1865d).
`true` if the container contains no elements; otherwise, `false`.
Removes the highest-priority element of the container.
For more information, see [priority_queue::pop (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/d363b3f1-247b-466a-a300-c5918b0dfd4e).
Adds a new element to the container.
For more information, see [priority_queue::push (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/317d3feb-0688-4658-866b-a26cae060354).
An element to insert into the controlled sequence.
The controlled sequence is then reordered to maintain the heap discipline.
Counts the number of elements in the container.
For more information, see [priority_queue::size (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/37ef4be3-daac-4b5a-9a00-085863f694e0).
The length of the controlled sequence.
Accesses the highest-priority element of the container.
For more information, see [priority_queue::top (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/e45211d5-e6df-4c03-97fd-57afb87af58c).
The top (highest-priority) element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Accesses the highest-priority element of the container.
For more information, see [priority_queue::top_item (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/d497403b-6b1d-4c6e-a0f4-c744cc5fad75).
The top (highest-priority) element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Copies the ordering delegate for two elements.
For more information, see [priority_queue::value_comp (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/af28e541-087d-4837-9ff0-cd36d4cfc57a).
The ordering delegate used to order the controlled sequence.
You use it to compare two values.
